he Act. * * * * * PART 212_DOCUMENTARY REQUIREMENTS: NONIMMIGRANTS; WAIVERS; ADMISSION OF CERTAIN INADMISSIBLE ALIENS; PAROLE 4. The authority citation for part 212 continues to read as follows: Authority: 8 U.S.C. 1101, 1102, 1103, 1182, 1184, 1187, 1225, 1226, 1227, 1228, 1252; and 8 CFR part 2. 5. In §212.1, paragraph (e)(4)(i) is revised to read as follows: §212.1 Documentary requirements for nonimmigrants. * * * * * (e) *␣*␣* (4) *␣*␣* (i) Adjustment of status to that of a temporary resident or, except under the provisions of section 245(i) of the Act, to that of a lawful permanent resident; * * * * * PART 217_VISA WAIVER PILOT PROGRAM
